#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:4
msgid "Areas"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:6
msgid ""
"The application window is always a rectangle on your desktop. It is "
"divided up into a number of re-sizable areas. An area contains the "
"workspace for a particular type of editor, like a 3D View Editor, or an "
"Outliner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:13
#, fuzzy
msgid "Arranging"
msgstr "Disponiendo áreas"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:15
msgid ""
"Blender uses a novel screen-splitting approach to arrange areas. The idea"
" is that you split up that big application window into any number of "
"smaller (but still rectangular) non-overlapping areas. That way, each "
"area is always fully visible, and it is very easy to work in one area and"
" hop over to work in another."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:23
#, fuzzy
msgid "Changing the Size"
msgstr "Cambiando el Tamaño del Área"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:25
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can resize areas by dragging their borders with :kbd:`LMB`. Simply "
"move your mouse cursor over the border between two areas, until it "
"changes to a double-headed arrow, and then click and drag."
msgstr ""
"Puede redimensionar las áreas al arrastrar sus bordes con :kbd:`LMB`. "
"Simplemente mueva el cursor sobre los bordes entre dos áreas hasta que "
"éste cambie a una flecha doble, y entonces haga click y arrastre."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:31
msgid "Splitting and Joining"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:34
msgid "Area Split Widget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:39
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the upper right and lower left corners of an area are the area split "
"widgets, and they look like a little ridged thumb grip. It both splits "
"and combines areas. When you hover over it, your cursor will change to a "
"cross (✛)."
msgstr ""
"En la zona superior derecha y en la inferior izquierda de un área están "
"los controles para dividir áreas, y éstos se ven como un pequeño agarre "
"en forma de huellas digitales. Sirven tanto para dividir como para "
"combinar áreas. Cuando se deslice sobre ellos, su cursor cambiará a una "
"cruz. Haga click con :kbd:`LMB` y arrastre hacia la izquierda para "
"dividir el área de la ventana verticalmente, o hacia abajo para dividirlo"
" horizontalmente."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:43
msgid ""
":kbd:`LMB` and drag it inward *split* the area. You define the direction "
"of that border by either dragging horizontally or vertically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:46
msgid ""
"In order to *join* two areas :kbd:`LMB` click and drag the area splitter "
"outward. They must be the same dimension (width or height) in the "
"direction you wish to join. This is so that the combined area space "
"results in a rectangle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:53
msgid "The Properties Editor is being merged \"over\" the Outliner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:55
msgid ""
"The area that will closed gets a dark overlaid with an arrow. Now you can"
" select the area to be closed by moving the mouse over it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:58
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Release the :kbd:`LMB` to complete the join. If you press :kbd:`Esc` or  "
":kbd:`RMB` before releasing the mouse, the operation will be aborted."
msgstr "Si presiona :kbd:`Esc` antes de soltar el ratón, la operación se abortará."

